The paper deals with the problem of Matrix Scaling, which is a fundamental problem in numerical linear algebra and has applications in various areas such as preconditioning linear systems and approximation of the permanent. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Numerical Analysis (cs.NA), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM), Computational Complexity (cs.CC), and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
